# Matveyevka, Republic of Bashkortostan

}}
Matveyevka () is a rural locality (a village) in Pervomaysky Selsoviet, Sterlitamaksky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 206 as of 2010. There are four streets in the village.
Geography
Matveyevka is located 23 km southwest of Sterlitamak, the district's administrative centre, by road.
